# Copy this file to ".env" (next to app.py) and fill in your values.
# The app loads it at startup so the Copilot SDK subprocess inherits these —
# useful for corporate proxies when launching by double-click. The real .env is
# gitignored. Existing environment variables are NOT overridden.
#
# Corporate proxy (include credentials inline if your proxy requires auth):
# HTTPS_PROXY=http://user:password@proxy.example.net:8080
# HTTP_PROXY=http://user:password@proxy.example.net:8080
# NO_PROXY=localhost,127.0.0.1,.example.net
#
# Alternatively, point at an existing .env without copying it, by setting
# COPILOT_ENV_FILE (e.g. in run.bat) to its full path.
